# USER_Guide.md must stay current

When changing `ppdm-k8s-pvc-restore/` scripts, update `ppdm-k8s-pvc-restore/USER_Guide.md` in the same task if behavior, prompts, arguments, defaults, or troubleshooting change.

## Update these sections

| Change type | USER_Guide sections |
|-------------|---------------------|
| New/changed interactive prompt | Step 2 workflow (2a–2f) |
| New/changed script argument | 2f Restore execution, Non-interactive usage |
| New/changed env var or default | Environment variables table |
| New/changed error or log message | Troubleshooting |
| API or cluster prep behavior | Restore type (PPDM API), Requirements |

## Source of truth

- Wrapper: `pvc_restore_wrapper.sh` (prompts, `run_restore` positional args)
- Restore: `ppdm-restore-selected-pvcs-api.sh` (`usage()`, argument parsing, defaults)

Do not leave USER_Guide describing removed behavior (e.g. live `kubectl get pvc` listing, automatic target namespace creation).
